correctness.rationale: Major schema violations, incorrect units, and untraceable/speculative values. Examples: (1) Many numeric fields are null/None despite schema requiring numbers and the task forbidding nulls: processParameters.thicknessControl.growthPerCycle.numberofCycles.numericValue, thicknessControl.nucleationPeriod.numericValue, dosingTime.coReactant.numericValue, purgeTime.precursor/coReactant.numericValue, flowRates.precursorFlow/coReactantFlow/purgingGasFlow.numericValue, supercycleDesign.numberofSubcycles.count.numericValue, materialProperties.uniformity.variation.numericValue, conformality.aspectRatio.numericValue, filmComposition.elementalConcentration.values.quantityValue.numericValue, optical/electrical property numeric values, roughness.value, filmDensity.value, deviceProperties.onOffRatio.numericValue. (2) Unit errors: dosingTime uses unit MilliSEC (ms) but values are given in seconds (1.5 s, 0.1 s) without conversion; subthresholdSwing is reported as 0.24 with unit MilliV, but the article states 0.24–0.25 V/dec; it should be 240–250 mV (or unit V with 0.24–0.25). (3) Unsupported/speculative values: growthPerCycle set to 0.29 Å for In2O3, Ga2O3, ZnO is not provided in the article text; filmComposition.atomicRatio '1.0:2.8:5.4' is not reported; carrierGas and purgingGas set to 'Ar' are not explicitly stated for carrier/purge (only Ar/O2 plasma is specified). (4) Schema structure violation: growthPerCycle object contains an extra property 'filmThickness' which is not allowed (additionalProperties: false). (5) Missing/placeholder values: crystallinity.phase is 'Not Found' though the article reports composition-dependent phases (amorphous, ZnO(100), In2O3 cubic); reactor fields 'Not Found' are not grounded. (6) While some entries are correct (PEALD method, precursors DADI/TMGa/DEZ, co-reactant Ar/O2 plasma, temperature 200 °C, plasma power 300 W, pressure ≈1.2 Torr, film thickness 20 nm for TFT channel, mobility 41.4 cm2/V·s, Vth −1.0 V), the prevalence of nulls, unit mistakes, and untraceable values renders the extraction largely incorrect. Correct by removing placeholders/nulls or populating with traceable values, fixing units (convert s→ms, report SS as 240–250 mV), deleting unsupported GPC/atomic ratio, and conforming to the schema structure.

completeness.rationale: Bad completeness. While some core parameters match the article (PEALD method for In2O3/Ga2O3/ZnO; DADI/TMGa/DEZ; Ar/O2 plasma; 200 °C; 1.2 Torr; 300 W; substrates; 20 nm channel; mobility and Vth), many fields are missing, schema-noncompliant, or inconsistent with the text. Key issues: (1) Numerous required or included fields have null/placeholder values, violating schema and the no-empty-values rule: growthPerCycle.numberofCycles, growthPerCycle.filmThickness, nucleationPeriod, dosingTime.coReactant, purgeTime entries, all flowRates, uniformity.variation, conformality.aspectRatio, filmComposition.elementalConcentration.values, crystallinity.phase, roughness.value, filmDensity.value, device onOffRatio. (2) Unit/numerical inconsistencies: precursor dosing times are reported in seconds (DADI=1.5 s; TMGa=0.1 s; DEZ=0.1 s) but encoded as MilliSEC with unconverted numeric values (should be 1500 ms and 100 ms); subthreshold swing is 0.24 V/dec but encoded as 0.24 MilliV (should be 240 mV if using MilliV). (3) GPC values (0.29 Å for all oxides) are not supported by the provided text (GPC data are in SI Figure S1) and appear confounded with lattice spacings (0.29 nm) from TEM; thus likely incorrect. (4) SupercycleDesign.numberofSubcycles counts are left null and no a:b:c ratios are provided, despite the study focusing on composition control via supercycles; at least one explicit supercycle ratio or tie-line example (e.g., In:Ga:Zn = x:3.3:1.0 or y:1.0:1.7) should be captured. (5) Film composition is inaccurate/incomplete: atomicRatio '1.0:2.8:5.4' is not traceable to the article; the paper provides composition regions and tie-lines and an optimal range (XIn 0.56–0.63, XGa 0.13–0.17, XZn 0.17–0.34), which should be reflected. (6) Missing characterization method labels where stated: bandgap by Tauc plot, electrical by Hall, crystallinity by XRD/TEM. (7) Crystallinity information is left 'Not Found' despite detailed phases reported for composition regions; the selected process should specify the appropriate phase for the corresponding composition. (8) Multiple processes: the article discusses several composition sets (e.g., L1 and L2 tie-lines and multiple samples), but only a single generic process is extracted without clearly mapping to a specific composition; at minimum, separate processes for representative compositions (e.g., optimized high-mobility case(s)) should be provided. Properties to add/review: correct dosingTime units; add purge and plasma exposure times if available or omit non-required fields instead of null; provide supercycle subcycle counts or explicit a:b:c ratios; provide composition (Xi) consistent with the optimal region; supply crystallinity phase for the chosen composition; correct SS units; remove fabricated GPC or replace with SI values; add film density values from XRR for representative samples; include characterization methods (Tauc plot, Hall, XRD/TEM); provide on/off ratio if reported.
